# Language Boundaries

Use this rule to keep language usage consistent across implementation and documentation.

## Code and machine artifacts

- Write code artifacts in English.
- This includes identifiers, constants, enum values, machine keys, API/schema field names, and code comments/docstrings.
- Keep machine-readable keys ASCII and stable; do not introduce locale-specific keys.

## Requirement specifications

- Requirement specifications under `spec/requirements/` must be written in German.
- Use proper German spelling with umlauts (`ä`, `ö`, `ü`, `Ä`, `Ö`, `Ü`) and `ß` where appropriate.
- Technical identifiers may remain in English when needed for precision.

## Technical documentation

- Technical manuals and operational documentation under `doc/` may be written in German or English.
- Choose one primary language per document and keep wording consistent within that document.
